Identify complete proteins

identify_complete_genes=function(x=files_G495A, path="../data/BUSCO_genes/G495_A_sample14/"){
  res = vector(length = length(x))
  for (i in 1:length(x)) {
  s=read.fasta(paste0(path,x[i]))
  codon=as.character(getFrag(s[[1]], 1,3))
  if (sum(codon==c("a","t","g"))==3) res[i]=TRUE
  }
  return(res)
}

files_G495A_complets=identify_complete_genes(x = files_G495A, path="../data/BUSCO_genes/G495_A_sample14/")

Identify common genes found in the four strains

common_files=intersect(intersect(files_G495A[files_G495A_complets], files_Lb84A[files_Lb84A_complets]) , files_SiennaA[files_SiennaA_complets])
common_files=intersect(common_files, files_StFoyA[files_StFoyA_complets])
length(common_files)
## [1] 409
G495_busco_nucleotide=list()
Lb84_busco_nucleotide=list()
Sienna_busco_nucleotide=list()
StFoy_busco_nucleotide=list()

for (i in 1:length(common_files)) {
  G495_busco_nucleotide[[i]]=read.fasta(file = paste0("../data/BUSCO_genes/G495_A_sample14/", common_files[i]))
  Lb84_busco_nucleotide[[i]]=read.fasta(file = paste0("../data/BUSCO_genes/Lb84_A_sample26/", common_files[i]))
  Sienna_busco_nucleotide[[i]]=read.fasta(file = paste0("../data/BUSCO_genes/Sienna_A_sample47/", common_files[i]))
  StFoy_busco_nucleotide[[i]]=read.fasta(file = paste0("../data/BUSCO_genes/StFoy_A_sample19/", common_files[i]))

  busco_gene_set=c(G495_busco_nucleotide[[i]], Lb84_busco_nucleotide[[i]], Sienna_busco_nucleotide[[i]], StFoy_busco_nucleotide[[i]])
  
  # remove last codon because the presence of STOP codons produce strange behaviour for downstream applications:
  busco_gene_set = lapply(X = busco_gene_set, FUN= function(x){
      x = getFrag(object = x, begin = 1, end = getLength(x)-3)  
      return(x)
  })
  
  busco_prot_set=c(getTrans(busco_gene_set[1]), getTrans(busco_gene_set[2]), getTrans(busco_gene_set[3]), getTrans(busco_gene_set[4]))
  write.fasta(sequences = busco_prot_set, file.out = paste0("../data/BUSCO_genes/", common_files[i]), names = c("G495", "Lb84", "Sienna", "StFoy"))
 
   # write CDS
  file_out2=paste0("../data/BUSCO_genes/", common_files[i])
  file_out2=paste0(file_out2, "_cds.fa")
  write.fasta(busco_gene_set, file.out = file_out2, names =c("G495", "Lb84", "Sienna", "StFoy"))
 
  # align prot
  input=paste0("../data/BUSCO_genes/", common_files[i])
  mySequences <- readAAStringSet(input)
  myFirstAlignment <- msa(mySequences)
  aln <- msaConvert(myFirstAlignment, type="seqinr::alignment")
  write.fasta(sequences = lapply(aln$seq, as.vector), file.out = paste0(input, ".aln"), names =c("G495", "Lb84", "Sienna", "StFoy"))

  # reverse align CDS
  file_out3=paste0(input, "_rev_aln.aln")
  reverse_aln=reverse.align(nucl.file = file_out2, protaln.file = paste0(input, ".aln"), input.format = "fasta", out.file = file_out3, output.format = "fasta")

  
  }

Calculate dN and dS

dNdS_busco=list()

for (i in 1:length(common_files)){
    # orf number
  orf_name=common_files[i]
  aln_file=paste0("../data/BUSCO_genes/", orf_name)
  aln_file=paste0(aln_file, "_rev_aln.aln")
  alignment=read.alignment(aln_file, format = "fasta")
  
  # length of the alignment (in nucl)
  length_aln=unlist(lapply(X = alignment$seq, FUN=function(x){
    return( nchar(x))
  }))
  mean_aln_length=mean(length_aln)
  
  res=kaks(x = alignment)

  dNdS_busco[[i]]=res
  }

# remove the genes where the calculation failed
which_NA=lapply(dNdS_busco, FUN=function(x) {
  nas=is.na(x[1])
  }
  )

dNdS_busco = dNdS_busco [-which(unlist(which_NA))]

which_extreme=lapply(dNdS_busco, FUN=function(x) {
  # test the presence of dS abnormally elevated
  res=sum(x[[2]]>1)
  res=res>0
  return(res)
  }
  )

dNdS_busco = dNdS_busco [-which(unlist(which_extreme))]

# final number of genes for which dS is calculated:
length(dNdS_busco)
## [1] 321

Average dS over all genes

dS_matrix=lapply(dNdS_busco, FUN = function(x){
  return(x[[2]])
})

my_matrix=dS_matrix[[1]]
for (i in 2:length(dS_matrix)){
  my_matrix=my_matrix+dS_matrix[[i]]
}

# divide by the number of estimations to get an average dS :
dS_matrix_final=my_matrix/length(dNdS_busco)

dS_matrix_final
##               G495        Lb84      Sienna
## Lb84   0.003418166                        
## Sienna 0.001965520 0.002550005            
## StFoy  0.004136552 0.002539559 0.003420026
# plot the NJ tree
plot.phylo(x = nj(dS_matrix_final), type = "unrooted", cex = 0.8, rotate.tree = 45)
add.scale.bar(length = NULL, ask = FALSE,
              lwd = 2, lcol = "black")
